<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871210-0074 </DOCNO><HL> Merchants BancsharesAnd United VermontDelay Their Merger</HL><DD> 12/10/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MBVT UVTBTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)BANKS, THRIFT INSTITUTIONS (BNK) </IN><DATELINE> BURLINGTON, Vt.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Merchants Bancshares Inc. and United Vermont Bancorp. of Rutland, Vt., said their previously announced merger has been delayed to allow additional &quot;due diligence to be performed.&quot; The merger was scheduled for completion tomorrow.    Under the terms, the two bank holding companies planned to merge into a new holding company to be named New England Merchants Bancshares Inc.    Each of United Vermont's approximately 1.2 million fully diluted common shares would be converted into 1.055 shares of the new holding company. Each of the 2.2 million common shares of Merchants Bancshares would be converted into one share of the new company.    Dudley H. Davis, president of Merchants, said the two banks &quot;need additional information&quot; and added that he &quot;doesn't know if terms will change.&quot; He said he anticipates that it will be &quot;several weeks&quot; before a new closing date is set.    United Vermont Bancorp. officials weren't available for further comment. </TEXT></DOC>